devalued, from all sides and at a constant&nbsp;pace.</p>\n\n<p>Anyone who loves the cinema needs to stand up for it. What I dont mean is the idea of movies as a kind of cultural messaging delivery service, which can actually play a part in the devaluation. What I do mean is the art of cinema.&nbsp;Period.</p>\n\n<p>Ive been <a href=\"/sight-and-sound/magazine/subscriptions\" title=\"Sight &amp; Sound subscriptions\">subscribing to Sight and Sound</a> for 60 years. And when I look through the pages of the latest issue, it always lifts my spirits. Why? Because its made and maintained by people who <em>care</em>.</p>\n\n<p>People who love our artform. Please keep it that&nbsp;way.</p>\n\n<p>Thank you for your recognition of Killers of the Flower&nbsp;Moon.</p>\n\n<drupal-paragraph data-embed-button=\"slice_articles\" data-paragraph-id=\"5346b75d-d296-42b8-a4e3-e024c12596e1\" data-paragraph-revision-id=\"715851\" data-paragraph-type=\"newsletter_signup\"></drupal-paragraph>","standfirst":"At the top of our best films of 2023 poll stands Scorseses late masterpiece, an epic story told in intimate terms about the systematic robbing and murder of the Osage of Oklahoma in the 1920s. Here he responds to his win.","films":["7ddf2db3-a39a-556d-b7cb-5ecb7a3132a6"],"hasHero":true,"imageAltText":null,"imageCaptionOverride":"Martin Scorsese (standing) directing Leonardo DiCaprio, Lily Gladstone and Robert De Niro on the set of Killers of the Flower Moon","imageCaptionAndCredit":false,"person":["18d0e853-93e1-50de-88be-af1a6a69e344"],"description":"The director responds to coming top of our Best Films of 2023 poll with Killers of the Flower Moon","seo_no_index":false,"seoTitle":"Martin Scorsese on making the best film of 2023"},"relationships":{"node_type":{"data":null,"links":{"self":{"href":"https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/api/article/95d098f7-c6fc-434a-9ff9-11b2842427ff/relationships/node_type?resourceVersion=id%3A74325"}}},"extraSlices":{"data":[],"links":{"related":{"href":"https: